    "body": "@becker33 @tgamblin @tldahlgren \r\n\r\nI would like to filter output of `spack test list` by installed specs instead of seeing all the specs with the spec syntax. \r\n\r\n### Rationale\r\n\r\nOutput of `spack test list` can be quite long it makes it easier to find specs that one may want to test. \r\n\r\n@tgamblin @becker33 @tldahlgren \r\n\r\nRight now i have to grep for specs to see what is available\r\n\r\n```\r\nshahzebsiddiqui@iris19:~> spack test list | grep libxml2 | head -n 3\r\ngahbtdd libxml2@2.9.10\r\ncqhyezh libxml2@2.9.10\r\nzmxcvsn libxml2@2.9.10\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat i'd like to do is say `spack test list libxml2` or `spack test list libxml2@2.9.10` or any of the spec syntax.\r\n\r\nRight now i can't do that since this argument is not available\r\n\r\n```\r\nshahzebsiddiqui@iris19:~> spack test list libxml2\r\n==> Error: unrecognized arguments: libxml2\r\n```\r\n\r\nI am using the e4s-21.02 tag at JLSE.\r\n\r\n",
